Vantiv Inc., a major U.S. credit-card processor, has made an offer valuing U.K. payments group Worldpay Group Inc. at $10 billon, potentially beating out rival bidder J.P. Morgan Chase & Co. Worldpay said in a statement Wednesday that it had agreed a deal in principle with Vantiv. The deal, if successful, would create a trans-Atlantic payments processing giant with a combined market value of more than $20 billion.

