Reply



Thank you. Your comment has been submitted and is pending editorial review.




  Submit Comment




1 Reply





By: CompareCards | May 25, 2017
If the merchant will allow you to pay with a credit card then the transaction should be considered a purchase. If you're looking for the longest possible intro APR, consider the Citi Simplicity or the Citi Diamond Preferred. These cards don't offer cash back, so if you'd like cash back plus a long intro period check out the Discover It Cashback Match.










